'''James George Janos'''<ref name=OWOW>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/profiles/j/jesse-ventura.html|title=OWOW profile}}</ref> (born July 15, 1951), best known as '''Jesse "The Body" Ventura''', is an American [[politician]], retired [[professional wrestling|professional wrestler]] and [[color commentator]], [[Underwater Demolition Team|Navy UDT]] [[veteran]], [[actor]], and former [[radio]] and [[television]] [[talk show]] host. As a professional wrestler, he is best known for his tenure in the [[World Wrestling Entertainment|World Wrestling Federation]] as a wrestler and color commentator. In 2004, he was inducted into the company's [[WWE Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]].<ref name=OWOW/>

In the [[Minnesota gubernatorial election, 1998|Minnesota gubernatorial election of 1998]], running as an [[Independence Party of Minnesota|Independent]] and member of the [[Reform Party of the United States of America|Reform Party]], he was elected the [[List of Governors of Minnesota|38th]] [[Governor of Minnesota]] and served from January 4, 1999 to January 6, 2003 without seeking a second term. 
==Early life==
Ventura was born James George Janos in [[Minneapolis]], the son of Bernice Martha ([[married and maiden names|n<U+00E9>e]] Lenz) and George William Janos. His father's parents were from what is today [[Slovakia]], and his mother was of German descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wargs.com/political/ventura.html |title=Ancestry of Jesse Ventura |publisher=Wargs.com |date= |accessdate=2008-10-20}}</ref> Ventura has described himself as [[Slovak American|Slovak]].<ref>April 1, 2008, in Larry King interview with Ventura on NBC<!--Bot-generated title--></ref> Ventura (then still using his legal name of Janos) attended the now-closed Cooper Elementary School, and graduated from Minneapolis' [[Roosevelt High School (Minneapolis)|Roosevelt High School]] in 1969.

From September 11, 1969 to September 10, 1975, during the [[Vietnam War]] era, he served in the [[United States Navy]].<ref name=OWOW/> While on active duty, Ventura was part of [[Underwater Demolition Team|Underwater Demolition Team 12]] (UDT).<ref name=slambio/> The UDT was merged with the [[United States Navy SEALs|US Navy SEALs]] in 1983, 8 years after Ventura was no longer in the Navy. He was awarded the [[National Defense Service Medal]] and the [[Vietnam Service Medal]] but was not in combat thus did not qualify for the [[Combat Action Ribbon]].

In 1973, Ventura was a full-patch member of the [[San Diego]] chapter of the [[Mongols (motorcycle club)|Mongols]], an [[Outlaw motorcycle club#One Percenters|outlaw]] motorcycle gang and [[organized crime syndicate]] for nine months, and rose to the rank of Sergeant-at-Arms. His [[nickname]] by Mongol members was "[[Superman]]". Ventura has said on ''[[The Howard Stern Show]]'' in 2009 that "once you're a Mongol, you're always a Mongol."<ref>[http://www.mikemooneyham.com/pages/viewfull.cfm?ObjectID=6DC12C2B-3048-52EA-1E11892F489953D7 One on One with Jesse Ventura]</ref><ref>[http://www.reviewjournal.com/lvrj_home/2002/May-12-Sun-2002/news/18724079.html OUTLAW GANGS: Northern Nevada eyes biker enmity]</ref>

He returned to [[Minnesota]], and attended [[North Hennepin Community College]] in the mid-1970s, at the same time he began [[Powerlifting|weightlifting]] and [[professional wrestling|wrestling]]. He was a bodyguard for [[The Rolling Stones]] for a short time before he ventured into professional wrestling and changed his name.<ref>[http://www.pbs.org/newshour/on2/elections/ventura.html Jesse Ventura] PBS</ref>

